CatDescriptText: Cutline of related images published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1962, pg. 14A, reads: " Holiday House Glistens With D.I.'s Style Show and Dance Benefit for MENDS, the National Foundation for Neuromuscular Diseases, Inc."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Terri Springer wearing light colored dress with pleats at waist, dark gloves, beaded necklace, and light colored floral hat, standing in front of musicians in the Holiday House for D.I. Club's "Melody in Fashion" benefit for MENDS
